Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the gnocchi. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @chicken thigh{210%g}(diced) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until browned on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}, turning occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once the pan of water is boiling, add the @gnocchi{500%g} and simmer until they float to the top, ~{2-3%minutes}. Drain well in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop them sticking together. Set aside for frying later. While the gnocchi cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @chives{1/2%bunch}(roughly chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Once the chicken has browned, add the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1%tbsp} to the pan and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the @tomato passata{1%400g can}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer gently until the chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the @creme fraiche{75%g} into the sauce. Bring back up to the boil, then add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large frying pan on high heat. Once hot, add the gnocchi and stir-fry until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}. Add the fried gnocchi to the sauce along with half the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated), then stir to combine.

When ready, divide the chicken gnocchi between your serving bowls. Sprinkle over the chives and the remaining @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) to finish. Enjoy!